overview: The user initiated a request for a comprehensive review of a sleep
  questionnaire application, aiming to ensure all acceptance criteria were met
  and to implement any identified missing features. The agent conducted a
  thorough review, identifying several key areas for improvement. Subsequently,
  the agent systematically implemented these features. This included adding a
  1-10 severity scale for tiredness with critical safety warnings, implementing
  detection and recommendations for COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea)
  and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, integrating a "Resources & Next Steps"
  section with relevant outbound links, and enhancing the Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness (EDS) scoring with weighted criteria. Additionally, the CSV export
  functionality was expanded to include all questionnaire data, and new
  questions related to pain severity and chronic fatigue screening were
  incorporated. The implementation followed a structured plan, addressing each
  identified gap to enhance the questionnaire's diagnostic capabilities and user
  guidance.
